               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360613-name-1391" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360613-name-1391" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360613-name-1391" type="surname" value="FAUNTLEROY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360613-name-1391" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS FAUNTLEROY</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Potter's-fields, and am ivory-mer<lb></lb>chant. On Tuesday, the 13th of May, I was in Tooley-street, and felt a tug at my coat pocket—I turned round suddenly and caught the prisoner's hand enclosing my handkerchief—I took it from him—I caught his hand and the handkerchief and the tail of my coat together—the handkerchief was all outside the pocket—it was gone from person, because my coat pocket dropped, and I took the handkerchief his hand.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I told you a boy that went along took it—you know well it was not me took the handkerchief—I told you it was another boy—you would not go after him <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. He told me it was put into his hand by another boy—he was close behind me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360613-name-1392" type="witnessName">
